<node id="Vans AU">
  <data key="d0">Vans AU</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Vans AU is an Australian brand that operates within the GRA storefront framework, specializing in shoes and apparel. It is particularly recognizable for its distinctive features, which include a staging URL that allows for Qantas Points and distinct navigation labels for its products. Vans AU has made efforts to improve user interactions on its product detail pages, contributing to a more streamlined experience for customers.

The brand also employs specific technical elements across its storefronts, helping maintain consistency in design and functionality. Located specifically as Vans Australia, it is known for rendering a full-page acquisition popup immediately upon homepage load. This feature is part of its engagement strategy, although it has faced criticisms for interfering with user actions on the authentication modal due to the Bloomreach acquisition popup.

Vans AU operates not just in Australia but also extends its services to New Zealand, aiming to enhance the shopping experience through tailored navigation patterns and cart button designs. The brand's initiatives reflect a focus on improving usability and interactions across various touchpoints for its customers.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-18c320b704b53c1b59c41f904f29e640-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;doc-e06ad78290d5db25f3a4f84c2e156204-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-003</data>
  <data key="d4">ecommerce-storefronts.md&lt;SEP&gt;gra-storefront-tech-notes.md&lt;SEP&gt;ecommerce-auth-modal-gotchas.md&lt;SEP&gt;ecommerce-pdp-page-gotchas.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1783308738</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
  <data key="d7">Vans AU</data>
</node>
<node id="Dr. Martens AU">
  <data key="d0">Dr. Martens AU</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Dr. Martens AU is an Australian subsidiary of the globally recognized footwear company Dr. Martens, renowned for its distinctive shoes and boots that have become iconic within various subcultures and counterculture movements. The brand has a notable retail presence in Australia and New Zealand and is characterized by certain technological and design specifications, such as a shared cart button hash similar to that of Vans.

The e-commerce platform of Dr. Martens AU features a dedicated staging URL that allows customers to utilize Qantas Points for purchases. However, it faces specific challenges, including navigation quirks and issues related to product count display on the Product Listing Page (PLP), often returning zero when accessed through the `getTotalProductCount()` function. Additionally, the brand exhibits similarities in technical characteristics to others under investigation within the GRA storefront, particularly regarding the lack of initial session tracking.

Overall, Dr. Martens AU represents a fusion of distinct brand identity and modern e-commerce challenges, positioning itself uniquely in the competitive footwear market in Australia.&lt;SEP&gt;The Australian branch of the Dr. Martens brand known for its footwear, mentioned alongside Skechers AU in the context of design decisions.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-18c320b704b53c1b59c41f904f29e640-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cf017a813cd0b782aef34bc894b9789d-chunk-001&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cf017a813cd0b782aef34bc894b9789d-chunk-002&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-89278d88eec2b6ee50a522529e8ddbde-chunk-000</data>
  <data key="d4">ecommerce-storefronts.md&lt;SEP&gt;gra-storefront-tech-notes.md&lt;SEP&gt;ecommerce-smoke-spec-catalog.md&lt;SEP&gt;ecommerce-pdp-page-gotchas.md&lt;SEP&gt;e2e-chkout-004-shipping-method.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1784615429</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
  <data key="d7">Dr. Martens AU</data>
</node>
<node id="Dr. Martens NZ">
  <data key="d0">Dr. Martens NZ</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">A New Zealand brand of Dr. Martens that does not earn Qantas Points and has unique navigation issues.&lt;SEP&gt;The corresponding brand to Dr. Martens AU, matching in technical setups as part of GRA storefronts.&lt;SEP&gt;A New Zealand counterpart to Dr. Martens AU, sharing various digital properties and technologies.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific storefront location for Dr. Martens in New Zealand, identified in relation to modal title race conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The New Zealand division of Dr. Martens, which has encountered strict-mode violations due to rendering multiple H1 elements on product detail pages.&lt;SEP&gt;An organization involved in e-commerce, specifically related to the New Zealand market for footwear and apparel.&lt;SEP&gt;A footwear company known for its distinctive boots, typically available in multiple colorways, suggesting a wide variety for product testers.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-18c320b704b53c1b59c41f904f29e640-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-e06ad78290d5db25f3a4f84c2e156204-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-004&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-cecb0d91ce73637998acce9c5c61beac-chunk-002</data>
