<node id="GraphQL">
  <data key="d0">GraphQL</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A query language for APIs and a runtime for fulfilling those queries with existing data, emphasized in the TypeScript coding rules.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphQL is a query language for APIs, enabling clients to request only the data they need and perform complex queries in a single request, used in the context of the Magento application for handling requests efficiently.&lt;SEP&gt;A data query language that allows for interactive and efficient data retrieving from APIs, which is utilized in Magento 2 for handling address data.&lt;SEP&gt;A query language for APIs and a server-side runtime for executing those queries with existing data.&lt;SEP&gt;A query language for APIs that allows clients to request specific parts of data, facilitating efficient data fetching in the eCommerce context.&lt;SEP&gt;A query language for APIs and a runtime for fulfilling those queries with existing data, used for creating fresh accounts in the testing process.</data>
  <data key="d3">doc-cc4fd56733f33ebf5767403007d22d7f-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-13c6ca4c338ad773242cc059a8049dc9-chunk-003&lt;SEP&gt;doc-13c6ca4c338ad773242cc059a8049dc9-chunk-005&lt;SEP&gt;doc-c9488069466f7da02e04d0a79614e167-chunk-005&lt;SEP&gt;doc-a74540e7570b89ad3bb5cb22795ee605-chunk-000&lt;SEP&gt;doc-3b6ffa939ea42d6f764cbf5263f0a48f-chunk-000</data>
